#Introduction:
This document describes the testing strategy, scope, resources, schedule, and deliverables for testing the Healthcare Management System application.

The objective is to ensure that the application meets the functional and performance requirements before release.

#Scope of Testing:
The following modules will be tested:
    • User Registration
    • User Login
    • Patient Management
    • Appointment Booking
    • Billing System
    • Insurance Validation
    • Reports Genaration

      Out of Scope:
    • Third-party payment gateway testing
    • Hardware device testing
    • Performance testing beyond defined scope

#Test Objectives:
The objective of testing is to:
    • Validate application functionality
    • Ensure system stability
    • Identify defects before release
    • Verify business requirements

#Testing Types:
The following testing types will be performed:
    • Functional Testing:
      Verify application features work according to requirements.

    • Integration Testing:
      Verify communication between modules such as:
       1. Appointment and Billing
       2. Billing and Insurance        
      
    • Regression Testing:
      Ensure new changes do not affect existing features.
      
    • API Testing:
      Verify back end APIs using Postman.
      
    • Usability Testing:
      Ensure Application is user-friendly.

#Test Environment:

Component           Configuration
OS                     Linux
Browser              Chrome, Firefox
Database              MySQL
API Tool             Postman
Bug Tracking Tool     Jira
Automation Tool      Selenium

#Test Data:
Test data will include:
    • Valid patient records
    • Invalid input data
    • Duplicate entries
    • Boundary values

#Test Deliverables:
The following document will be produced:
    • Test Plan
    • Test Scenarios
    • Test Cases
    • Bug Reports
    • Test Execution Report
    • Test Summary Report

#Entry Criteria:
Testing will start when:
    • Application build is deployed
    • Requirements document is approved
    • Test environment is ready

#Exit Criteria:
testing will stop when:
    • All critical defects are fixed
    • Test cases are executed
    • Test coverage is completed
    • Test summary report is prepared

